06/07/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer visited Zagreb on Thursday (6 July), meeting with President Stipe Mesic, Prime Minister Ivo Sanader and other government members before heading on to Tirana.
Talks in Zagreb focused on implementation of defence reforms, Croatia's bid for NATO membership and increased participation in international peacekeeping missions abroad.
On Friday, de Hoop Scheffer visits Athens.
(NATO Web site, HRT - 06/07/06)
